  "text": "In in vivo condition average tuber weight and tuber number were determined as different depending on the production technique (Leifert and Struik, 1992; . [CITATION_1] found that the tuber numbers of various potato cultivars were between 6.2 to 7.9 in plantlets grown in polyethylene bags. In the study of minituber production, result showed that plants which were directly transplanted into field represented best result than other substrates.",
